      ],
      "phrases": [
        {
          "text": "Where they know they will find me, with my maps and faith in the distance, moving farther on.",
          "track": 3
        },
        {
          "text": "They were cutting from stone some dreams of their own, but they listened to mine anyways.",
          "track": 4
        },
        {
          "text": "In the end, they traded their tired wings, for the resignation that living brings, and exchanged love's bright and fragile glow for the glitter and the rouge.",
          "track": 8
        },
        {
          "text": "While they scuffled for your weary smiles, I thought of all the empty miles and the years that I'd spent looking for your eyes.",
          "track": 2
        }
      ]
    },
